eur-industriel/carte-des-implantations/centrale-nucleaire-de-saint-alban/presentation Centrale nucl\u00e9aire de Saint-Alban]\n| extra                  = \n}}\n\nThe '''Saint-Alban nuclear power plant''' is located on the [[Rhone]] river, in the [[Is\u00e8re]] department 50&nbsp;km downstream from [[Lyon]] in the communes of [[Saint-Alban-du-Rh\u00f4ne]] and [[Saint-Maurice-l'Exil]].\n\n==Description==\nThe power station uses water from the Rhone river to cool its two 1,300 MW reactors and employs 670 people..\n\n==Type of reactors==\nThe following types of reactors are installed:\n\n==Reactor units==\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"  \n|- \n! Reactor Unit<ref name=\"IAEA\">[http://www.iaea.org/programmes/a2/ Power Reactor Information System] from [[International Atomic Energy Agency|IAEA]]: [http://www.iaea.org/cgi-bin/db.page.pl/pris.powrea.htm?country=FR&sort=&sortlong=Alphabetic \"France (French Republic): Nuclear Power Reactors\"] {{in lang|en}}</ref>\n! Type\n! Average Output\n! Rated Power\n! Began construction\n! Finish construction\n! Commercial operation\n! Close of reactor\n|-\n| St.Alban-1 || [[Pressurized water reactor|PWR]] || 1381 MW || 1335 MW||Jan 1979 || Aug 1985 ||May 1986 || \n|-\n| St.Alban-2 || [[Pressurized water reactor|PWR]] || 1381 MW || 1335 MW ||July 1979 || July 1986 ||March 1987 ||\n|-\n|}\n\n.<ref name=\"IAEA2\">http://www-pub.iaea.org/MTCD/publications/PDF/CNPP2010_CD/pages/AnnexII/tables/table2.htm\n</ref>\n\n==Seismological risk==\nAccording to [[WENRA]], EDF has prepared a plan in case of an earthquake,<ref>WENRA [https://web.archive.org/web/20120320234848/http://www.wenra.org/dynamaster/file_archive/110307/30f176179f606b68a33835f0033859ac/RHWG_Report_harmonisation_existing_NPPs_Feb2011.pdf Progress towards harmonisation of safety for existing reactors in WENRA countries] (p 74/88)</ref> however other ASN documents from 2002 there may be some anomalies regarding the remote control and which may put into question the correct functioning of certain elements following an earthquake.\n\n==2003 heatwave==\nFollowing extremely high temperatures in July 2003 average water temperature rose above the limit authorised by the nuclear safety authorities for a period of 4 hours.\n\n== Fire risk ==\n\nAccording to the 2007 ASN annual report recommendations were made to the operator to improve the security of the control room.<ref>{fr} {{cite web |url=http://www.asn.fr/sections/rubriquesprincipales/publications/rapport-annuel-asn/liste-rapports-annuels/2006/chapitre-12-centrales-nucleaires-d-8217/downloadFile/attachedFile_f0/RA-2006-Chapitre-XII-.pdf?nocache=1175506163.3 |title=Archived copy |access-date=2011-09-12 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929084324/http://www.asn.fr/sections/rubriquesprincipales/publications/rapport-annuel-asn/liste-rapports-annuels/2006/chapitre-12-centrales-nucleaires-d-8217/downloadFile/attachedFile_f0/RA-2006-Chapitre-XII-.pdf?nocache=1175506163.3 |archive-date=2007-09-29 |df= }}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n{{stack|{{Portal|France|Energy|Nuclear technology}}}}\n* [[List of nuclear reactors#France|List of nuclear reactors - France]]\n\n== References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{fr} [https://web.archive.org/web/20100526180846/http://energies.edf.com/edf-fr-accueil/la-production-d-electricite-edf/-nucleaire/les-centrales-nucleaires/saint-alban-120051.html Saint-Alban Power station website]\n\n{{French nuclear power plants}}\n\n[[Category:Nuclear power stations in France]]\n[[Category:Energy infrastructure completed in 1985]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Is\u00e8re]]\n\n[[no:Saint-Laurent kjernekraftverk]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox power station\n| name                   = Saint-Alban Nuclear Power Plant\n| name_official          = Centrale nucl\u00e9aire de Saint-Alban\n| image                  = Centrale Nucl\u00e9aire de Saint-Alban.jpg\n| image_size             = \n| image_caption          = Overview over the power plant site\